Your message has been rejected because you posted a binary to a
non-binary newsgroup. It often happens with users of Netscape who use
Cyrillic (KOI8) letters. Most of the readers of this newsgroup would not
be able to read your posting. If this is the case, please correct
settings in your Options menu.

The program that detects binaries has just been installed, so please let
scrm-admin@algebra.com know if your posting was a non-binary that was
improperly rejected.  Read charter of soc.culture.russian.moderated in

	http://www.algebra.com/~ichudov/usenet/scrm/index.html

Please direct your queries to scrm-board@algebra.com.

Thank you,

	- Moderator.
